---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms of Use - Der Town"
  description="Terms of use for Der Town community platform. Learn about our guidelines and policies for using our community events and announcements service."
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-linear-to-br from-indigo-600 to-indigo-900 flex items-center justify-center py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-95 rounded-lg shadow-lg max-w-2xl w-full p-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Effective Date: May 7th, 2025</p>
      <p class="mb-6 text-gray-800">Welcome to Der Town! This site provides a community calendar and announcements for events in and around Leavenworth WA. By using this site or submitting content through our web form, you agree to the following terms:</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-6 text-gray-900">
        <li>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-900 mb-1">Event Submissions</h2>
          When you submit an event or announcement via our web form, you grant us permission to publish, edit, and publicly display that content on this site and in related materials (e.g., newsletters or social media). We may make minor edits for clarity, formatting, or space.<br/>
          <span class="italic">Do not submit private or sensitive information—submissions are publicly viewable.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-900 mb-1">Content and Copyright</h2>
          Some event details and descriptions may be compiled or quoted from third-party websites. All such content remains the property of its original copyright holders and is used here under fair use or with attribution where applicable.<br/>
          If you are a rights holder and wish to have content updated or removed, please email us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-900 mb-1">Community Standards — Objectionable Content</h2>
          We have <strong>zero tolerance for objectionable content or abusive behavior</strong>. This includes content that is hateful, harassing, threatening, sexually explicit, violent, discriminatory, deceptive, or otherwise harmful. All submissions are reviewed before publication, and we may reject or remove any content at our sole discretion.<br/>
          You can report content from the mobile app (Report buttons on events, announcements, and organizations) or by emailing us. <strong>We act on reports within 24 hours</strong> by removing content that violates these terms and barring repeat offenders from submitting. Users of the mobile app can also block an organizer to immediately hide that organizer's content from their feed.
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-900 mb-1">Disclaimer</h2>
          We strive to provide accurate information but cannot guarantee the correctness, completeness, or availability of any event listed. Always confirm event details with the organizer.
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-900 mb-1">Changes to These Terms</h2>
          We may update these Terms of Service from time to time. Continued use of the site after changes means you accept the updated terms.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout> 